{
  "mcpServers": {
    "marketing-analytics": {
      "command": "python3",
      "args": ["/Users/martinstolk/Projects/Mia/brain/mcp_server.py"],
      "env": {
        "GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID": "${GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID}",
        "GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET": "${GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET}",
        "GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN": "${GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN}",
        "GA4_PROPERTY_ID": "${GA4_PROPERTY_ID}",
        "META_APP_ID": "${META_APP_ID}",
        "META_APP_SECRET": "${META_APP_SECRET}",
        "PYTHONPATH": "/Users/martinstolk/Projects/Mia/brain"
      }
    }
  }
}

<!-- 
To use this configuration with Claude Desktop:

1. Copy this configuration to your Claude Desktop MCP settings file:
   - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
   - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
   - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

2. Set your actual environment variables by replacing ${VAR_NAME} with actual values:
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID: Your Google OAuth client ID
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET: Your Google OAuth client secret  
   - GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN: Your Google Ads developer token
   - GA4_PROPERTY_ID: Your Google Analytics 4 property ID
   - META_APP_ID: Your Meta app ID (optional)
   - META_APP_SECRET: Your Meta app secret (optional)

3. Update the path in "args" to match your actual installation path

4. Restart Claude Desktop

